# TURN 6 — Security & Validation Layer — Walkthrough

## Summary

Added packet signing (SHA256), timestamp freshness validation, and duplicate detection to the hospital federated learning system. The server now rejects tampered, stale, or duplicate packets before accepting updates.

## Changes Made

### [NEW] [security.go](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/문서/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/security.go)

- [verifySignature(packet)](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/security.go#19-41) — recomputes `SHA256(json(metadata) + SecretKey)` and compares to `packet.Signature`
- [validateTimestamp(packet)](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/security.go#42-64) — rejects packets older than 30 seconds (also rejects future timestamps)

### [MODIFY] [packet.go](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/문서/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/step-01/hospital/packet.go)

- `Metadata.Timestamp` changed from `string` → `int64` (Unix epoch)
- Added `Signature string` field to [UpdatePacket](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/main.go#23-28)
- Added [SignPacket()](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/step-01/hospital/packet.go#46-57) method and `SecretKey` constant
- [GenerateUpdatePacket()](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/step-01/hospital/packet.go#58-91) now sets timestamp and signs before returning

render_diffs(file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/문서/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/step-01/hospital/packet.go)

### [MODIFY] [main.go](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/문서/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/main.go)

- Extended [Metadata](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/client_simulator.go#20-28) with `Timestamp int64` and [UpdatePacket](file:///c:/Users/SARIGASINI/OneDrive/Desktop/%EB%AC%B8%EC%84%9C/GitHub/hospital_federated_learning/server/main.go#23-28) with `Signature string`
- `/submit_update` handler pipeline: **Decode → Verify Signature → Validate Timestamp → Field Checks → RoundManager → Store**

